analysis.key_observation: Major dump from $67.8k to $64.3k (5.2% drop) in early trading, now recovered to $66.1k - classic capitulation bounce pattern

data.price_action: After a -5.2% flash crash from $67.8k to $64.3k, BTC has recovered nearly 3% and is now consolidating around $66.1k-$66.5k. Price is trading ABOVE the VWAP ($65,829) suggesting buyers have regained control.
data.volume_analysis: 7324 BTC traded during the crash hour (10x normal) - classic capitulation volume. Volume has normalized since, suggesting panic selling exhausted.

bullish_factors: Price recovered 3% from lows - V-shaped bounce
Consolidation forming higher lows last 4 hours
risk_factors: Still -2% on the day - macro pressure
Need to reclaim $67k for trend reversal
Could be dead cat bounce before further drop
